>Ranganathan_Chakravarthy: ILOO M6 OLIO +12 277
#note this move also took ranganathan a while to finalize.
>JD: CEGIPST 4K .G +6 265
#note I spent an eternity on this move trying to choose between a 1-tile or two-tile fish. ultimately, quackle noticeably prefers GIP at N4, which I probably should've considered more seriously; it bingos at a 53% clip versus the 70% rate after UG. I went through and figured out all the letters in the bag that bingoed after UG and eventually felt comfortable playing it. I can fish with GOBO for an extra point, but it actually sims almost identical because GOBO prevents OBOE overlaps for EPICIST/SEPTICS.
